review_title: SENSE OF PRIDE - MOTIVATION TO RESIST TEMPTATION SENSE OF PRIDE - MOTIVATION TO RESIST TEMPTATION
review_text: In one experiment, three groups of people were invited to a room with chocolate cakes in turn. The first group was reminded of the guilt they would experience after eating the cake. The second was asked to think about how proud they would be of their willpower if they could resist the temptation. The third group was not given instructions. And here is the result: those whose pride the experimenters cried out for ate the least of all. Conclusion: Feeling proud is better at resisting temptation than feeling guilty. Shame and guilt absorb the strength needed to fight temptation. Pride, on the other hand, gives energy that feeds the will to resistance. This fact is of some importance in resisting such common human weaknesses as overeating, procrastination, and laziness.

Psyllium is a fiber obtained from the seed coats of certain types of plants, particularly psyllium seeds. These fibers have several health benefits, especially for the digestive system. Here are some of them: 1. Improves digestion: Psyllium has the ability to retain water and form a thick, jelly-like mass in the intestines. This helps improve intestinal motility and eases the passage of the intestinal walls, which can help with bowel movements and prevent constipation. 2. Lowering Cholesterol: Eating psyllium can help lower total and "bad" cholesterol in the blood. This is due to the ability of psyllium to bind fats in the intestines and reduce their absorption. 3. Blood sugar control: Psyllium can help stabilize blood sugar, especially beneficial for people with type 2 diabetes. Psyllium fiber can slow the process of blood sugar rising after eating. 4. Maintaining a healthy weight: Psyllium can help with weight control by providing a feeling of satiety and reducing appetite. Psyllium fibers absorb water, expand in the intestines and create a feeling of fullness. 5. Support for healthy gut microflora: Psyllium may help support healthy gut microflora, which is important for overall digestive health and immune function. 6. Reduce inflammation: Some studies have shown that psyllium may have anti-inflammatory properties that may be helpful in reducing inflammation in the body. These beneficial properties of psyllium make it a popular dietary supplement to support digestive health and overall well-being.

review_title: HOW TO BECOME A HEALTHY PERSON: 3 PILLARS OF HUMAN HEALTH
review_text: ‚úîÔ∏è Proper nutrition. Proper nutrition helps to keep the physical body in order. Do not rush to extremes. Each person is completely individual and everyone needs to eat as much as they need. An excess or lack of food will lead to only one result - to constant thoughts about food. How to determine the necessary amount of food for a person? The best way is to get up from the table with a slight feeling of hunger. This is when a person feels that he can eat more, but it is already possible not to eat. In this case, a person will not have any heaviness in the stomach, he will not fall asleep after eating, and he will feel very light. The most favorable order of eating: sweet, then salty and at the end something airy and light. ‚úîÔ∏è Proper sleep. Proper sleep helps keep the mind in order, first of all. There are 5 things that depend on normal sleep: Human happiness (there is no normal sleep - no mood, no happiness); Digestion of food (important processes in the body occur precisely in sleep; therefore, a healthy, normal sleep is necessary); Human strength (with normal sleep there is natural strength); The ability to procreate (it is impaired with bad sleep); Knowledge and ignorance (if a person sleeps a lot or late, he sinks into ignorance). Sleep is a very important factor affecting human health. Unfortunately, so many people are careless about sleep and don't sleep properly. You don't need to force yourself to sleep too little. If you need to sleep, you better sleep. But remember that in matters of sleep, as in matters of nutrition, it is better to be a little underslept than a little overslept. The norm of sleep is determined individually. Waking up to an alarm clock is not very good. You need to learn to get up without an alarm clock. ‚úîÔ∏è Ordered sex. Chastity allows us to realize our spiritual nature. Chastity is a careful attitude to sexual (reproductive) energy. The length of a person's life depends greatly on this energy. If a person is very passionate about sex, spending sexual energy, then this will adversely affect health and spiritual well-being. Of course, you can have sex only with your beloved husband or beloved wife. Be moderate in this matter, as well as in matters of nutrition and sleep. Excessive sex addiction is especially dangerous for men ‚Äî they become weak as a result
